popular.title: The Voice
popular.synopsis: America's votes determine which four artists will advance to the live finals.
popular.series_synopsis: Singers compete for a record contract and $100,000.

popular.title: Chicago PD
popular.synopsis: A mass shooting takes place in an athletic club; Halstead and Platt try to check up on Lindsay.
popular.series_synopsis: District 21 of the Chicago Police Department is composed of the uniformed cops, who deal with street crimes, and the Intelligence Unit, which deals with major crimes like drug trafficking and high-profile murders. Sgt. Hank Voight -- a tough boss who doesn't mind bending the rules a little in the pursuit of justice -- heads the unit's elite team. The responsibilities of life on the force take a toll on the officers, as they struggle to balance their personal lives with the strain of the job. From Emmy-winning producer Dick Wolf.

popular.title: The Blacklist
popular.synopsis: Red must use his connections to clear Liz's name when she realizes she is being framed by The Cabal.
popular.series_synopsis: When former government agent and fugitive Raymond "Red" Reddington surrenders to the FBI, he makes them an offer they can't refuse. On the mysterious condition that he work only with recent Quantico graduate Liz Keen, he agrees to help put away criminals from a list that he compiled, which includes politicians, mobsters, spies and international terrorists -- starting with long-thought-dead terrorist Ranko Zamani. As the two pursue their quarry, Red forces the rookie profiler to think like a criminal to see the bigger picture.

popular.title: Days of our Lives
popular.synopsis: Relationships grow and die in the town of Salem.
popular.series_synopsis: Set in the town of Salem, this long-running soap opera follows the triumphs and tragedies of the Horton, Brady and DiMera families. Love and family stories intertwine with more suspenseful yarns, ratcheting up the drama quotient. Love triangles, murder, amnesia, rape, divorce, and other staples of the afternoon soap opera abound.

popular.title: Chicago Fire
popular.synopsis: Cruz and Boden put their lives on the line when a warehouse blaze gets out of control.
popular.series_synopsis: When the squad members of Chicago Firehouse 51 lose one of their own, there is more than enough guilt and blame to go around. Lt. Matthew Casey, who is dealing with a divorce, tries to move past the loss but can't help being at odds with the Rescue Squad's Lt. Kelly Severide, because the two blame each other for what happened to their fallen friend. Regardless of personal tension, when it's time to face the job, all the team members quickly put their issues aside and their lives on the line.

popular.title: Law & Order: Special Victims Unit
popular.synopsis: Efforts to find a boy kidnapped for ransom are hindered by his contentious estranged parents.
popular.series_synopsis: Detectives who are part of the NYPD's Special Victims Unit investigate crimes against the vulnerable. While the focus of other shows in the "Law & Order" franchise largely deal with murders, the SVU detectives frequently deal with rape and assault, in which a survivor assists in the investigation. The series cast of veteran actors include Mariska Hargitay and rapper Ice-T, and occasional crossover episodes feature detectives from other series in the "Law & Order" franchise.

popular.title: Dateline NBC
popular.synopsis: A mother is murdered in a home invasion the day before her best friend is shot outside her office.
popular.series_synopsis: Lester Holt hosts this newsmagazine that delivers in-depth coverage of news events and investigates subjects of all kinds. NBC news correspondents probe crimes, trends and issues to present long segments, and sometimes full one- or two-hour broadcasts.

popular.display_episode_title: The Mystery of the Deceased Documentarian
popular.title: The Mysteries of Laura
popular.synopsis: An amateur detective clashes with the team during an investigation into a filmmaker's death.
popular.series_synopsis: Laura Diamond is a brilliant NYPD homicide detective striving to balance her day job with a chaotic home life, and she's the first to admit that she doesn't always pull it off flawlessly. Her rambunctious twin boys and soon-to-be ex-husband, Jake - who can't seem to find the time to sign the divorce papers - make life interesting. Complications arise when Jake becomes Laura's boss at the precinct, but with the help of her understanding - and attractive - partner, Billy, she somehow manages to make it all work.

popular.title: The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon
popular.synopsis: TV show host Bill O'Reilly; Snoop Dogg performs with The Roots.
popular.series_synopsis: The long-running late-night talk show returns to New York for the first time since 1972 when comic Jimmy Fallon takes over hosting duties, accompanied by his Grammy-winning house band, The Roots. The former cast member of "Saturday Night Live" and lead of a later show welcomes guests to an evening of comedy, music, conversation and competitions. Lorne Michaels serves as the program's executive producer.

popular.title: Late Night With Seth Meyers
popular.synopsis: Actress Anna Kendrick; actor Thomas Middleditch; comic Tom Scharpling; musician Jon Wurster.
popular.series_synopsis: The former "Saturday Night Live" cast member and head writer follows on the heels of fellow SNL alumnus Jimmy Fallon to become the fourth host of the late-night NBC series. Armed with his sharp wit, Meyers welcomes celebrity guests, comedy and musical talent to the stage.
